original: Cerenius, David Emanuel, kyrkoherde, Lysekil, f. 3/4/98 i Gbg. G. 22 m. Anna Kullberg. Barn: Karin f. 23, stud., Gösta 28, stud. — Stud:ex. i Lund 15, teol. fil. ex. 17, teol. kand. o. prakt. teol. prov 19, prästv. f. Gbgs stift 20. V. pastor i Ölmevalla 20, i Fagered 21, kyrkoadj. i UddevaMa 22, kommin. där 29, kyrkoh. i Lysekil sed. 47. Led. av kyrkofullm. o. kyrkoråd.
translated: Cerenius, David Emanuel, clergyman, Lysekil, born on March 4th, 1898 in Gothenburg. Married in 1922 to Anna Kullberg. Children: Karin, born in 1923, a student, Gösta, born in 1928, also a student. He passed the student final exams in Lund in 1915, passed his filosophical and theological exams in 1917, passed practical theological exams in 1919, and ordained as a priest for the diocese of Gothenburg in 1920. He was a vicar in Ölmevalla in 1920, in Fagered in 1921, a church adjutant in Uddevalla in 1922, a curate there in 1929, and became the parish priest in Lysekil in 1947. He is a member of the church council.
